# Autonomous Agricultural Rover

ROS2 Jazzy-based autonomous rover for R'Garden Community Garden at UCR.

## Team
6-person robotics team, 4-week development sprint

## System Overview

### Hardware
- **Compute**: Raspberry Pi 5
- **Motor Control**: Raspberry Pi Pico
- **Navigation Sensors**: RPLIDAR A1, BNO055 IMU, NEO-M8N GPS
- **Obstacle Detection**: 4x HC-SR04 Ultrasonic
- **Environmental Sensors**: BME680, TSL2591, Soil moisture, MLX90640 thermal

### Software Architecture
- **ROS2 Jazzy**: Navigation, SLAM, sensor fusion
- **Nav2**: Autonomous path planning
- **SLAM Toolbox**: Mapping and localization
- **MQTT**: Environmental data to Lenovo server for Esri mapping

## Repository Structure
```
├── rover_description/     # URDF robot model
├── rover_navigation/      # Nav2 configs, SLAM, mission planning
├── rover_drivers/         # Sensor drivers (GPS, IMU, LiDAR, motors)
├── rover_bringup/         # Top-level launch files
├── pico_firmware/         # Motor control firmware
├── env_data/              # Environmental data collection (non-ROS)
├── calibration/           # Sensor and wheel calibration data
└── tests/                 # Unit and integration tests
```

## Setup

### Prerequisites
- ROS2 Jazzy on Ubuntu 24.04
- Python 3.12+

### Installation
```bash
# Clone repository
cd ~
git clone git@github.com:your-username/solara-rover.git

#mac users: 
#run docker
#cmd+shift+p: reopen in container 

#First Time Dev Container Setup
After opening in container for the first time:
```bash
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "your@email.com"
```

#everyone

cd solara-rover


# Install ROS2 dependencies
sudo apt install ros-jazzy-nav2-bringup \
                 ros-jazzy-slam-toolbox \
                 ros-jazzy-robot-localization \
                 ros-jazzy-rplidar-ros

# Install Python dependencies
pip3 install -r requirements.txt

# Build 
#Windows users
make sure you are in the root directory of the repo
colcon build 

# Source
source install/setup.bash
```

## Usage

### Hardware Testing
```bash
# Test individual sensors
ros2 run rover_drivers gps_driver
ros2 run rover_drivers imu_driver

# Launch all sensors
ros2 launch rover_drivers all_sensors.launch.py
```

### Navigation
```bash
# Full system launch
ros2 launch rover_bringup robot.launch.py
```

